<emphasis id="B923EAF4FF83FFF8FF57FF00FE4AFF43" bold="true" box="[151,387,151,176]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Material examined.</emphasis>
MBC-A 
<date id="FFE91026FF83FFF8FE2CFF0FFD88FF43" box="[492,577,152,176]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="31-02-22">022231</date>
; MBC-A023323; MBC-A027708; MBC-A027736; MBC-A077817; MBC- A077815; MBC-A077813; MBC-A077816.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836E6FF83FFF8FF07FF74FD85FED3" blockId="36.[151,1437,151,544]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B923EAF4FF83FFF8FF07FF74FEB9FF0F" bold="true" box="[199,368,227,252]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Identification.</emphasis>
Test sub-conically raised; apical zone bare, without tubercles except those circling periproct. Spines brightly banded red and yellow.
</paragraph>
